1
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:34,136
(Azure Spring)

2
00:00:34,137 --> 00:00:36,572
(All characters, places, events, etc. depicted are fictional.)

3
00:00:36,573 --> 00:00:39,075
(Children and animals were filmed under strict guidelines.)

4
00:00:45,815 --> 00:00:46,950
Teach me...

5
00:00:47,884 --> 00:00:48,885
how to dive and harvest.

6
00:01:00,096 --> 00:01:01,097
What are you doing?

7
00:01:01,831 --> 00:01:04,434
Are you going to teach me or not?

8
00:01:09,773 --> 00:01:11,574
I don't think I can do that.

9
00:01:16,479 --> 00:01:17,480
Hey!

10
00:01:17,814 --> 00:01:18,982
I can do it, too!

11
00:01:19,722 --> 00:01:21,424
I said, I can do it!

12
00:01:25,822 --> 00:01:27,390
How can he say something like that?

13
00:01:27,657 --> 00:01:28,858
What a punk.

14
00:01:34,197 --> 00:01:40,203
(Episode 2: Troublemaker Cat)

15
00:01:58,154 --> 00:02:00,757
Gosh, that was the worst sleep ever.

16
00:02:27,817 --> 00:02:30,086
Fine. You go and enjoy all your fancy diving...

17
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,921
all by yourself.

18
00:02:36,359 --> 00:02:38,962
What? He didn't go out to dive?

19
00:02:42,065 --> 00:02:43,066
Hey.

20
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:46,636
You punk... I mean, Mr. Haenam?

21
00:02:49,205 --> 00:02:50,240
Are you around?

22
00:02:51,141 --> 00:02:52,175
Hey.

23
00:02:54,778 --> 00:02:55,779
No?

24
00:03:09,125 --> 00:03:11,061
Darn it. Never mind.

25
00:03:33,116 --> 00:03:34,884
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

26
00:03:37,554 --> 00:03:38,755
Please be here.

27
00:03:39,656 --> 00:03:40,824
Please be here.

28
00:03:52,736 --> 00:03:55,071
I knew it. My mom is the only one...

29
00:03:56,006 --> 00:03:57,140
who's willing to back me up.

30
00:04:00,110 --> 00:04:02,612
You got this, An Na!

31
00:04:03,146 --> 00:04:04,880
- You can do it! - Let's go!

32
00:04:04,881 --> 00:04:06,215
Let's do this!

33
00:04:06,216 --> 00:04:07,483
Let's go!

34
00:04:07,484 --> 00:04:08,584
(Go, Parang-ri Mermaid Seo An Na)

35
00:04:08,585 --> 00:04:10,553
- You can do this! - Good luck!

36
00:04:11,721 --> 00:04:14,357
- You're the best! - Let's go!

37
00:04:17,627 --> 00:04:20,130
- Go! - You got this!

38
00:04:22,866 --> 00:04:24,934
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

39
00:04:48,224 --> 00:04:49,659
Why can't I put this on?

40
00:04:50,627 --> 00:04:51,628
Darn it.

41
00:04:52,228 --> 00:04:53,463
Come on.

42
00:05:15,552 --> 00:05:16,920
- You can do this! - You'll win!

43
00:05:17,253 --> 00:05:18,455
Let's go!

44
00:05:18,755 --> 00:05:20,856
- You can do this! - Let's go!

45
00:05:20,857 --> 00:05:22,892
- Good luck! - Go!

46
00:05:23,159 --> 00:05:24,193
Go get them!

47
00:05:24,194 --> 00:05:25,595
You got this!

48
00:05:39,209 --> 00:05:41,478
You got this, An Na!

49
00:05:41,711 --> 00:05:45,448
- Seo An Na! - You can do it, An Na! Good luck!

50
00:05:54,624 --> 00:05:56,492
(103rd National Swim Meet, 400m)

51
00:05:56,493 --> 00:05:58,461
(7. Seo An Na, Daehan Sports High School)

52
00:06:33,563 --> 00:06:35,198
Ready, go!

53
00:06:51,748 --> 00:06:52,782
To be honest,

54
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:55,452
it doesn't have to be harvesting seafood.

55
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:12,736
(Go, Parang-ri Mermaid Seo An Na)

56
00:07:21,111 --> 00:07:22,445
It was to prove that the time...

57
00:07:26,116 --> 00:07:27,584
that stopped for me that day...

58
00:07:31,554 --> 00:07:33,857
could start moving again.

59
00:07:46,303 --> 00:07:48,171
That was all I ever wanted.

60
00:08:25,408 --> 00:08:26,509
Darn it.

61
00:08:28,511 --> 00:08:30,480
An Na... An Na!

62
00:08:54,671 --> 00:08:55,739
Where am I?

63
00:08:57,974 --> 00:08:59,042
The punk from earlier?

64
00:08:59,409 --> 00:09:00,910
I'm not asleep.

65
00:09:03,113 --> 00:09:06,016
What happened?

66
00:09:07,817 --> 00:09:08,918
You're up, so let's go.

67
00:09:14,724 --> 00:09:18,627
Wait, am I allowed to leave just like this?

68
00:09:18,628 --> 00:09:21,731
Of course. You've been asleep for 12 hours.

69
00:09:26,236 --> 00:09:27,904
I see. Thank you.

70
00:09:36,846 --> 00:09:39,115
Hey, did you bring me here?

71
00:09:39,382 --> 00:09:40,784
How did you find me?

72
00:09:41,618 --> 00:09:43,420
Did you pull me out of the water?

73
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:46,823
Wait, did you pull me out and do mouth-to-mouth...

74
00:09:47,257 --> 00:09:48,358
resuscitation...

75
00:09:51,194 --> 00:09:52,954
Was I supposed to just leave you there then?

76
00:09:54,064 --> 00:09:56,399
Well, that wasn't what I meant.

77
00:10:02,272 --> 00:10:04,407
Hey... Hey!

78
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:31,647
I should've just left you there.

79
00:10:39,276 --> 00:10:40,510
You've lost your mind, An Na.

80
00:10:43,079 --> 00:10:44,647
You already have a boyfriend...

81
00:10:44,648 --> 00:10:46,182
yet you let another guy kiss you.

82
00:10:50,186 --> 00:10:51,254
No.

83
00:10:52,122 --> 00:10:53,390
I didn't let him do it.

84
00:10:53,757 --> 00:10:55,725
That heinous man was the one who did it.

85
00:10:56,926 --> 00:10:57,961
Yes.

86
00:11:05,435 --> 00:11:06,536
Hey.

87
00:11:07,637 --> 00:11:09,271
I gave this a thought, and...

88
00:11:09,272 --> 00:11:11,908
- Do you eat abalone? - I do. Wait.

89
00:11:12,542 --> 00:11:14,176
What about abalone? That's random.

90
00:11:14,177 --> 00:11:15,845
- How about hijiki? - I do.

91
00:11:17,347 --> 00:11:19,215
I'm trying to talk. Why are you...

92
00:11:25,488 --> 00:11:27,857
Why are you so full of yourself?

93
00:11:28,224 --> 00:11:29,926
I thought the kitchen was a common area.

94
00:11:30,093 --> 00:11:31,661
No, not that.

95
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:35,910
You mean the mouth-to-mouth resuscitation?

96
00:11:37,968 --> 00:11:39,569
Yes, that.

97
00:11:42,038 --> 00:11:43,473
I mean, sure.

98
00:11:43,773 --> 00:11:45,308
Thank you for saving me,

99
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:47,744
but I have...

100
00:11:49,145 --> 00:11:50,480
a boyfriend.

101
00:11:50,981 --> 00:11:52,048
So what?

102
00:11:54,017 --> 00:11:57,387
I'm already taken, so you can't just come up to me...

103
00:11:58,021 --> 00:11:59,822
and do that, putting me in a tough spot.

104
00:11:59,823 --> 00:12:01,103
You should've found another way.

105
00:12:01,391 --> 00:12:03,927
- I am looking for another way. - What?

106
00:12:04,427 --> 00:12:07,697
Abalones are good for freedivers, helping the lungs and bronchial tubes.

107
00:12:08,498 --> 00:12:11,601
Hijiki replenishes your minerals and calms your stomach.

108
00:12:16,172 --> 00:12:17,173
By any chance,

109
00:12:18,775 --> 00:12:20,076
are you looking after me?

110
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:26,148
Otherwise, you'll either steal my food or cause me trouble...

111
00:12:26,149 --> 00:12:27,250
by diving into the sea.

112
00:12:29,953 --> 00:12:31,353
Is that the only way you can speak?

113
00:12:53,376 --> 00:12:54,811
Come to think of it,

114
00:12:55,178 --> 00:12:57,147
my mom always had hijiki and abalones on days...

115
00:12:57,948 --> 00:12:59,916
when the sea was especially rough.

116
00:13:01,685 --> 00:13:03,586
Mom, I'm hungry.

117
00:13:04,321 --> 00:13:05,789
What's for dinner?

118
00:13:06,589 --> 00:13:09,559
I need to eat hijiki and abalones after a rough day out in the sea.

119
00:13:09,993 --> 00:13:11,461
I caught lots of abalones.

120
00:13:12,662 --> 00:13:16,032
Goodness, today was an extra tough day.

121
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:18,000
Gosh, that sounds delicious.

122
00:13:18,001 --> 00:13:20,270
I almost died back there.

123
00:13:24,307 --> 00:13:25,542
Goodness.

124
00:13:46,229 --> 00:13:49,099
All right. Here.

125
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,701
Freedivers have to sit in the cold sea all day,

126
00:13:52,936 --> 00:13:54,771
swallowing salty water endlessly,

127
00:13:57,073 --> 00:13:59,713
- and hold their breath countless times. - Looks good, doesn't it?

128
00:14:00,343 --> 00:14:02,383
So hijiki and abalone porridge was the best remedy.

129
00:14:49,693 --> 00:14:52,729
This is the best remedy when you fall in and swallow lots of water.

130
00:14:53,496 --> 00:14:55,498
I told you not to call it falling!

131
00:14:57,133 --> 00:15:00,470
Goodness. I'm glad to hear you shout.

132
00:15:02,072 --> 00:15:03,306
Eat up.

133
00:15:05,875 --> 00:15:10,080
It's definitely a little darker than a gold medal.

134
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,281
- Mom. - What?

135
00:15:12,282 --> 00:15:14,417
I like things that are darker.

136
00:15:15,051 --> 00:15:17,087
Look how dark it is. I love it.

137
00:15:18,822 --> 00:15:20,824
All right. Fine. Eat up.

138
00:15:27,364 --> 00:15:28,932
A bite of tender abalone...

139
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:30,900
slows down my heavy breathing.

140
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:39,776
And a crunchy piece of hijiki...

141
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:41,878
calms down my upset stomach.

142
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:02,432
The most nutritious dish for Parang-ri Mermaids...

143
00:16:03,667 --> 00:16:04,734
melts me completely,

144
00:16:06,636 --> 00:16:07,671
back then...

145
00:16:08,571 --> 00:16:09,739
and even now.

146
00:16:13,143 --> 00:16:14,444
You do your dishes.

147
00:16:19,316 --> 00:16:20,350
Seriously...

148
00:16:21,084 --> 00:16:22,452
Why is he so nice to me?

149
00:16:24,854 --> 00:16:26,356
Are you dating Coach Cha?

150
00:16:27,424 --> 00:16:28,792
What are you talking about?

151
00:16:29,059 --> 00:16:30,527
I have no time to date anyone.

152
00:16:31,361 --> 00:16:34,064
Watch out for guys who are nice to you.

153
00:16:34,397 --> 00:16:37,033
They're the sly ones, not anyone else.

154
00:16:42,205 --> 00:16:44,407
My mom told me to watch out for nice guys.

155
00:17:09,265 --> 00:17:10,834
I'll be careful if I need to,

156
00:17:11,968 --> 00:17:13,370
but I still need to thank him.

157
00:17:20,577 --> 00:17:21,678
Excuse me.

158
00:17:24,581 --> 00:17:25,649
What?

159
00:17:26,182 --> 00:17:27,784
Where does he go every morning?

160
00:17:41,698 --> 00:17:42,732
He's not here, either.

161
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:47,236
Hello, everyone. Today, I'll sing...

162
00:17:47,237 --> 00:17:49,305
my favourite song, "Oh My," for you.

163
00:17:49,306 --> 00:17:50,372
Two, three.

164
00:17:50,373 --> 00:17:53,977
Oh my, oh my, don't do this.

165
00:17:54,344 --> 00:17:55,879
Women's feelings are.

166
00:18:02,085 --> 00:18:03,619
Why are you glancing around?

167
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:04,687
Looking for someone?

168
00:18:04,688 --> 00:18:05,755
The punk...

169
00:18:06,089 --> 00:18:08,257
I mean, the freediver who lives at my place.

170
00:18:08,258 --> 00:18:10,293
Oh, you mean Duk Hyun?

171
00:18:11,061 --> 00:18:13,163
Around this hour, he's probably at...

172
00:18:14,297 --> 00:18:16,499
Wait, why are you looking for him?

173
00:18:16,766 --> 00:18:19,535
He made me some porridge,

174
00:18:19,536 --> 00:18:21,204
- but I never got to thank... - Porridge?

175
00:18:21,871 --> 00:18:24,140
He made you porridge?

176
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:26,876
Did he make it himself?

177
00:18:28,945 --> 00:18:31,481
Darn it. Hey! Yoon Duk Hyun!

178
00:18:32,115 --> 00:18:33,383
Where are you going?

179
00:18:34,451 --> 00:18:36,953
- Hey! - Duk Hyun!

180
00:18:37,387 --> 00:18:38,887
Yoon Duk Hyun!

181
00:18:38,888 --> 00:18:41,091
Where are you going, Su Jeong?

182
00:18:44,361 --> 00:18:45,595
Hey, Su Jeong!

183
00:19:11,955 --> 00:19:13,123
What's going on?

184
00:19:13,390 --> 00:19:15,358
I didn't know he could smile like that.

185
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:25,302
Duk Hyun.

186
00:19:27,804 --> 00:19:30,173
Did you make porridge for An Na?

187
00:19:35,145 --> 00:19:36,579
I did. What about it?

188
00:19:39,316 --> 00:19:40,417
How could this happen?

189
00:19:41,418 --> 00:19:42,552
Duk Hyun.

190
00:19:43,086 --> 00:19:45,288
I know we're living in a coastal village,

191
00:19:47,390 --> 00:19:50,327
but you can't play with my feelings!

192
00:19:51,728 --> 00:19:53,029
Why, Duk Hyun!

193
00:20:11,815 --> 00:20:14,451
Su Jeong had a misunderstanding.

194
00:20:16,653 --> 00:20:17,787
I don't care.

195
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:22,125
My goodness.

196
00:20:22,692 --> 00:20:24,594
You're such a punk.

197
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:31,768
I wasn't talking to you.

198
00:20:32,402 --> 00:20:35,338
These days, cats that act like a little menace...

199
00:20:35,605 --> 00:20:36,806
are called this,

200
00:20:37,674 --> 00:20:40,076
"troublemaker cats."

201
00:20:40,877 --> 00:20:42,579
You came this far to tell me that?

202
00:20:50,820 --> 00:20:52,022
Thank you.

203
00:20:55,992 --> 00:20:57,060
I forgot...

204
00:20:57,861 --> 00:20:59,496
to tell you this yesterday.

205
00:21:04,134 --> 00:21:05,235
It's all right.

206
00:21:06,002 --> 00:21:08,538
I wanted to prevent any future trouble.

207
00:21:09,105 --> 00:21:11,508
I also decided to thank you...

208
00:21:12,468 --> 00:21:14,604
because otherwise, it'll only make me look bad.

209
00:21:18,628 --> 00:21:20,096
Actually, when you said...

210
00:21:20,884 --> 00:21:22,118
you saw many who moved here...

211
00:21:23,386 --> 00:21:26,856
only to resent their failures without committing to anything,

212
00:21:29,592 --> 00:21:31,072
it felt like you were calling me out.

213
00:21:31,928 --> 00:21:33,029
It sounded just like me.

214
00:21:36,132 --> 00:21:37,834
I'm like that.

215
00:21:41,104 --> 00:21:42,906
Swimming is all I've done in my life.

216
00:21:44,507 --> 00:21:45,942
But I've become so broken...

217
00:21:46,943 --> 00:21:48,383
that I can't even fight the current.

218
00:21:52,282 --> 00:21:53,483
My life's pretty much ruined.

219
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,255
That was why I insisted...

220
00:22:00,056 --> 00:22:01,658
that I could be a freediver.

221
00:22:05,862 --> 00:22:07,902
Your life isn't ruined just because you can't swim.

222
00:22:11,368 --> 00:22:13,670
There are tons of people in the world who can't swim.

223
00:22:16,039 --> 00:22:18,274
I was an athlete, and...

224
00:22:18,275 --> 00:22:19,276
But now,

225
00:22:20,443 --> 00:22:22,512
you're just my landlord.

226
00:22:23,947 --> 00:22:25,882
There's no problem even if you can't swim.

227
00:22:31,755 --> 00:22:32,889
And just to let you know,

228
00:22:34,858 --> 00:22:37,727
when I said I couldn't teach you, I was talking about me.

229
00:22:39,229 --> 00:22:41,031
I'm an awful teacher.

230
00:22:49,472 --> 00:22:50,507
Can you...

231
00:22:52,208 --> 00:22:53,376
just try and teach me...

232
00:22:54,844 --> 00:22:55,879
how to harvest seafood?

233
00:22:59,382 --> 00:23:00,483
Both you and I...

234
00:23:01,851 --> 00:23:03,920
might be more talented than we thought.

235
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:18,768
Start by holding your breath.

236
00:23:29,045 --> 00:23:30,146
Wait for me!

237
00:23:48,965 --> 00:23:50,066
That's so salty!

238
00:23:55,305 --> 00:23:57,007
It's because this is seawater.

239
00:23:57,641 --> 00:24:00,176
I can hold my breath for up to three minutes in a pool.

240
00:24:01,444 --> 00:24:03,113
Do you harvest seafood in a pool?

241
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:04,581
Again.

242
00:24:05,615 --> 00:24:06,616
Darn it.

243
00:24:14,691 --> 00:24:17,661
Yoon Duk Hyun moved to Parang-ri three years ago...

244
00:24:18,094 --> 00:24:19,596
and began diving.

245
00:24:29,272 --> 00:24:32,475
He heads to the seashore alone whenever the tide is right,

246
00:24:32,943 --> 00:24:37,047
swims through the sea, dives underwater, and harvests seafood.

247
00:24:57,934 --> 00:25:00,136
Abalone, sea squirt,

248
00:25:01,271 --> 00:25:03,340
conch, and octopus.

249
00:25:04,407 --> 00:25:06,776
I watch him harvest these things given by nature.

250
00:25:07,844 --> 00:25:08,912
His life seems peaceful...

251
00:25:09,679 --> 00:25:10,847
and tranquil.

252
00:25:13,650 --> 00:25:15,151
I also want what he has.

253
00:25:18,688 --> 00:25:21,857
But to be honest, my worries tend to melt away...

254
00:25:21,858 --> 00:25:23,360
whenever I eat something delicious.

255
00:25:26,396 --> 00:25:27,597
Hey, there.

256
00:25:42,212 --> 00:25:45,248
Stir-fry some sliced garlic in olive oil.

257
00:25:48,385 --> 00:25:50,253
Then add some freshly caught seafood.

258
00:25:51,888 --> 00:25:53,189
It creates a fascinating flavour.

259
00:26:02,599 --> 00:26:04,434
Lastly, throw in some cooked ramyeon noodles.

260
00:26:06,102 --> 00:26:07,570
You won't find a better medicine.

261
00:26:12,475 --> 00:26:13,510
Come on.

262
00:26:14,177 --> 00:26:15,178
Dig in.

263
00:26:34,597 --> 00:26:35,665
Is it good?

264
00:26:55,485 --> 00:26:56,686
Duk Hyun said...

265
00:26:57,087 --> 00:26:58,588
there's absolutely no problem...

266
00:26:59,255 --> 00:27:01,057
even if I can't swim.

267
00:27:06,596 --> 00:27:07,697
Could that...

268
00:27:08,732 --> 00:27:09,866
be really true?

269
00:27:14,004 --> 00:27:15,738
And now, start skipping.

270
00:27:15,739 --> 00:27:18,508
Left, left, left.

271
00:27:22,245 --> 00:27:23,646
We're going downhill now.

272
00:27:23,647 --> 00:27:25,015
Are you going to stop here?

273
00:27:25,248 --> 00:27:27,317
Now, start skipping again.

274
00:27:28,585 --> 00:27:31,054
Left, left,

275
00:27:32,122 --> 00:27:33,189
left.

276
00:27:33,990 --> 00:27:36,792
- This isn't me trying to prove anything... - Left.

277
00:27:36,793 --> 00:27:38,161
Or throwing a tantrum.

278
00:27:39,596 --> 00:27:40,764
Wait up!

279
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:58,181
I'm just...

280
00:27:59,115 --> 00:28:00,483
curious...

281
00:28:10,260 --> 00:28:12,529
Could this freediver punk's words be true?

282
00:28:15,398 --> 00:28:17,634
Can I also be like him?

283
00:28:18,702 --> 00:28:20,470
What's the kind of peace...

284
00:28:21,271 --> 00:28:22,439
that he felt?

285
00:28:27,577 --> 00:28:28,778
I won, didn't I?

286
00:28:31,147 --> 00:28:32,827
I saw you lifting your face in the middle.

287
00:28:33,183 --> 00:28:34,284
Again.

288
00:28:34,551 --> 00:28:35,552
Darn it.

289
00:28:41,424 --> 00:28:43,693
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

290
00:28:45,261 --> 00:28:47,196
Lift your legs higher and stride wider!

291
00:28:47,197 --> 00:28:49,699
You're a former athlete! Did you train like this as a swimmer?

292
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,067
Darn it.

293
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:56,273
Whatever. I'm done.

294
00:28:57,073 --> 00:28:58,174
I'm done!

295
00:28:59,643 --> 00:29:00,777
Again!

296
00:29:01,177 --> 00:29:02,312
One more time.

297
00:29:03,647 --> 00:29:05,282
Do not give up. You can run back home.

298
00:29:06,116 --> 00:29:08,852
After I build up enough stamina to follow him into the sea...

299
00:29:10,987 --> 00:29:13,023
and get used to the salty seawater,

300
00:29:15,125 --> 00:29:16,226
could I...

301
00:29:16,693 --> 00:29:18,061
truly change?

302
00:29:34,878 --> 00:29:37,847
Will I ever be fine...

303
00:29:38,615 --> 00:29:40,583
even if I can't swim?

304
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:58,001
Today's training is over.

305
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:01,738
What are we eating today?

306
00:30:03,807 --> 00:30:04,874
We aren't done yet.

307
00:30:06,610 --> 00:30:08,678
What? We aren't done?

308
00:30:12,616 --> 00:30:14,284
It's time to go into the water.

309
00:30:42,912 --> 00:30:44,047
Will I...

310
00:30:44,881 --> 00:30:46,116
ever become...

311
00:30:47,450 --> 00:30:48,518
truly fine?

312
00:31:00,664 --> 00:31:02,699
She must've had a shoulder surgery.

313
00:31:08,672 --> 00:31:10,941
Does it look bad?

314
00:31:11,441 --> 00:31:13,710
It must've been a while since she had surgery,

315
00:31:14,044 --> 00:31:16,813
but I don't think that's why she drowned.

316
00:31:18,181 --> 00:31:21,817
Anyway, she fell asleep due to exhaustion,

317
00:31:21,818 --> 00:31:23,720
so don't worry and leave her here.

318
00:31:23,987 --> 00:31:25,655
All right. Thank you.

319
00:31:42,272 --> 00:31:43,406
Mom.

320
00:31:48,311 --> 00:31:50,146
My shoulder is fully healed.

321
00:32:00,490 --> 00:32:01,691
But...

322
00:32:05,795 --> 00:32:08,231
I don't think I can swim again.

323
00:32:15,872 --> 00:32:17,240
I'm sorry, Mom.
